<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 4:48AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Haskell, southeastern McIntosh and northeastern Pittsburg Counties
through 515 AM CDT...
At 448 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Arrowhead State Park, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Eufaula...                        Quinton...
Crowder...                        Canadian...
Arrowhead State Park...           Enterprise...
Blocker...                        Featherston...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
